      "side": 1,
      "message": "MD5 was chosen because it was the path of least resistance:\n\n* code already existed in GN\n* a self-contained (no deps), small, `unsafe`-free crate is readily available on crates.io\n\nI guess the first point above is easily fixable (hence this CL - thanks!), but the second one is not as clear to me.  Maybe adding SHA2 to GN and importing `sha-2` crate to Chromium is okay, but we\u0027d have to double-check that  (e.g. is `unsafe` and `asm!` ok?  what about the recommendation to prefer BoringSSL for crypto?).",
