      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am okay with this CL from Chromium\u0027s `//build/rust` perspective, because now I think that I can switch https://crrev.com/c/7226634 to use the self-contained https://docs.rs/hmac-sha256 crate.  This should mostly side-step open questions I raised above about:\n\n* BoringSSL\n    - Adding a new `//build/rust` \u003d\u003e `//third_party/boringssl` dependency\n* RustCrypto (e.g. `sha2` crate)\n    - In general we recommend to use BoringSSL instead.  This concern also applies to the `hmac-sha256` crate, but I think that it is okay there because it is a more self-contained crate and therefore doesn\u0027t seem as much as a slippery slope / double-standards.  And we will anyway limit GN `visibility` to `//build/rust/chromium_prelude`.\n    - There is a fair amount of `unsafe` and `asm!` (compared to a single [`unsafe`](https://github.com/jedisct1/rust-hmac-sha256/blob/718a8a8cdafa783a2a7b501f990ed7af23e52dfd/src/lib.rs#L78C22-L78C46) in the `hmac-sha256` crate).\n    - It has additional dependencies (e.g. the `digest` crate), unlike the self-contained `hmac-sha256` crate.",
